The paper deals with deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their plasticity in recovering from pruning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses fine-tuning and optimization techniques, which are common topics in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of filters and ranking criteria, which are relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Lastly, the paper evaluates object detection, which falls under the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
